), 
<number id="ED7E2417FFD2EF62C1E2F8F3FA3FF8CF" box="[1408,1436,1877,1901]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="15.0">15</number>
(
<number id="ED7E2417FFD2EF62C4C2F8DFFF1CF833" box="[160,191,1913,1937]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="10.0">10</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B093630FFD2EF62C4ABF83BFC97F87B" blockId="17.[151,1437,1301,2009]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD2EF62C4ABF83BFEC7F817" box="[201,356,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Male winged.</emphasis>
Smaller than female; body brown, mid and hind tibiae more extensively brown. Intermediate abdominal sternites without discal setae, pore plates absent.
</paragraph>
