<subSubSection id="13AC65BBFFD1EF61C4ABF8B3FD4DF81E" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5B093630FFD1EF61C4ABF8B3FD4DF81E" blockId="18.[151,1436,1596,1981]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD1EF61C4ABF8B3FEE4F88E" box="[201,327,1813,1836]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Comments.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9CB64DB3FFD1EF61C6C3F8B0FD56F88F" box="[673,757,1814,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Heterothripidae" genus="Heterothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD1EF61C6C3F8B0FD56F88F" box="[673,757,1814,1837]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9CB64DB3FFD1EF61C74EF8B3FC0EF88F" box="[812,941,1813,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Heterothripidae" genus="Heterothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD1EF61C74EF8B3FC0EF88F" box="[812,941,1813,1837]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having bicolored fore wings, discal setae on abdominal sternites, and no sternal pore plates in males. However, 
<taxonomicName id="9CB64DB3FFD1EF61C7A0F89FFB32F8F3" box="[962,1169,1849,1873]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sanctaecatharinae">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD1EF61C7A0F89FFB32F8F3" box="[962,1169,1849,1873]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sanctaecatharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an unusually short antennal segment IV and pronotum bears reticulate sculpture, rather than striate. The mesonotum is also not so closely striate, and the metanotal sculpture does not form a triangle. The adults are common inside flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="9CB64DB3FFD1EF61C1E5F827FEC5F81F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sanctaecatharinae">
<emphasis id="69C2EA22FFD1EF61C1E5F827FEC5F81F" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. sanctaecatharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, beneath the large yellow stamens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
